events.description: The Services PMI in Sweden fell to 54.3 in January 2026, indicating a slowdown in growth.

facts.fact_text: The Services PMI in Sweden fell to 54.3 in January 2026 from 56.3 in the previous month.

evidences.evidence_text: The Services PMI in Sweden fell to 54.3 in January 2026 from a downwardly revised 56.3 in the previous month.

facts.fact_text: The new orders sub-index dropped to 55.2 in January, a six-month low.

evidences.evidence_text: new orders, which dropped to 55.2 from 59.5 in December, reaching a six-month low.

facts.fact_text: The employment index fell to 49.7 in January.
The index for raw and intermediate goods prices rose to 60.1, the highest level in a year.

evidences.evidence_text: the index for raw and intermediate goods prices rising to 60.1, the highest level in a year, from 59.5 in December.

claims.claim_text: It is too early to determine if the current slump in services activity is temporary.
claims.author: Jörgen Kennemar

evidences.evidence_text: It is too early to determine whether it is a temporary slump or not.

claims.claim_text: The current slowdown in services activity is likely temporary due to company optimism.
claims.author: Jörgen Kennemar

evidences.evidence_text: Companies are still optimistic in their business plans, which suggests that it is a temporary slowdown.

evidence.evidence_text: This marked the softest pace of growth since August 2025 and brought the index below its historical average of 55.6.
Additionally, price pressures in the services sector intensified, with the index for raw and intermediate goods prices rising to 60.1
All major sub-indices declined, led by new orders, which dropped to 55.2 from 59.5 in December
